  script_tag(name:"insight", value:"OpenOCD, an on-chip JTAG debug solution for ARM and MIPS systems, does not block attempts to use HTTP POST for sending data to localhost, which allows remote attackers to conduct cross-protocol scripting attacks, and consequently execute arbitrary commands, via a crafted web site.

For Debian 7 Wheezy, these problems have been fixed in version 0.5.0-1+deb7u1.

We recommend that you upgrade your openocd packages.

